<topic template="Default" modified="2024-03-25T10:49:00.505Z" lasteditedby="44785" version="2" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../helpproject.xsd">
  <title>How do I Edit, Save, and Move my Styling?</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>Styling<keyword>Settings</keyword><keyword>Style</keyword><keyword>Theme</keyword></keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">... edit, save, and move my Styling</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_">How to edit your Settings, Styles and Theme.</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">We call the<text styleclass="VariableName"> Style</text><text styleclass="Body Text">, </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Theme, </text><text styleclass="Body Text">and</text>&#32;<text styleclass="VariableName">Settings</text> the <text styleclass="VariableName">Styling</text>.</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text">Each time you exit </text><text styleclass="VariableName">MechDesigner</text><text styleclass="Body Text">, we save for you the </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Styling</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> to </text><text styleclass="VariableName">MechDesigner.INI</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> and </text><text styleclass="VariableName">MechDesigner.XML.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="VariableName">MechDesigner</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> uses the </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Styling</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> automatically the next time it starts. </text></para>
    <para styleclass="VariableName">Styling Definitions:</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="3" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:106px;">
          <para styleclass="VariableName">Theme : </para>
        </td>
        <td style="width:599px;">
          <para styleclass="VariableName">Border, Icon, and dialog colors. </para>
          <para styleclass="Body Table">Use <text styleclass="VariableName">Application Settings : General tab &gt; </text><text styleclass="Separator">Theme Settings </text><text styleclass="VariableName"> &gt; Target Theme</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Table">Select one of these <text styleclass="VariableName">Themes</text>: </para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Windows, Charcoal Dark Slate, Aqua Light Slate, Windows10 Dark, Tablet Dark, Slate Classico, Windows10 Slate Gray, Windows 10.</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">Note, this help uses Charcoal Dark Slate.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:106px;">
          <para styleclass="VariableName">Style : </para>
        </td>
        <td style="width:599px;">
          <para styleclass="VariableName">Load a Style</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">Click the <link displaytype="button" type="topiclink" href="">Load<title>Load button</title></link><text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text>button to open a Style</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="VariableName">Dark.XML</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> - use with dark themes, for example, Charcoal Dark Slate. </text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="VariableName">Light.XML</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> - use with light theme, for example, Aqua Light Slate.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#343400;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName">Save a Style</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">Click the <link displaytype="button" type="topiclink" href="">Save<title>Save button</title></link><text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text>button<text styleclass="VariableName">:</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Save any changes you have made to Style file-name</para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName"><text style="color:#ff0000;">Do NOT overwrite Dark.XML or Light.XML.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:106px;">
          <para styleclass="VariableName">Application Settings : </para>
        </td>
        <td style="width:599px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal">Edit icon-sizes, number-formats and colors for different elements<text styleclass="Body Text">:</text></para>
          <list id="0" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="VariableName-indent" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="VariableName-indent">Application-Settings &gt; Graphics tab &gt; <text styleclass="Separator">Display Colors</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">There are many other settings you can make to suit your preferences. </para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Notes">Note</text>: You can also save and load these with the Save and Load buttons</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#343400;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Notes">Note</text>: </para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="VariableName">&lt;CommonAppData&gt;</text> is usually <text styleclass="VariableName">C:\ProgramData\</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text">If you cannot see <text styleclass="VariableName">C:\ProgramData\ .</text>.. then, i<text styleclass="Body Text HowTo">n </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Windows File Explorer:</text></para>
    <list id="1" type="ol" listtype="lower-alpha" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#41;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Click the <text styleclass="VariableName">View</text> tab<text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Click the <text styleclass="VariableName">Hidden Items</text> check-box in the <text styleclass="VariableName">Show/hide</text> group-box. </li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#343400;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_"><anchor id="SaveStyle"><keywords><keyword>Save the Style</keyword></keywords></anchor>Save your Styling</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">To save your styling:</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <list id="2" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Bullets" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI&apos;; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Bullets"><text styleclass="T_Menu">Edit menu &gt; Application-Settings</text>&#32;<text styleclass="VariableName">: </text><text styleclass="Body Text">Click the </text><text styleclass="ParameterHeader">Save</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> button at the bottom of the dialog.</text></li>
          </list>
          <list id="3" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="3" styleclass="Body Table" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Body Table">Save your styling. E.g.: <text styleclass="VariableName">&lt;CommonAppData&gt;\Style\My-style-name.XML </text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="VariableName" style="color:#ff0000;">DO NOT OVERWRITE</text><text styleclass="Normal">&#32;</text>the styles that are already in this path<text styleclass="Normal">. </text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_">Move your Styling</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">To move your styling to different computers</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="VariableName">On the source workstation:</para>
          <para styleclass="B Bullets">Save your <text styleclass="Body Text">styling</text> - see <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="" anchor="SaveStyle">preceding section</link>.<text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Remember, </text><text styleclass="VariableName" style="color:#ff0000;">DO NOT OVERWRITE</text><text styleclass="Normal"> the </text><text styleclass="Body Text">files already in the </text><text styleclass="VariableName">style</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> path.</text></para>
          <list id="4" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="B Bullets" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="B Bullets"><text styleclass="Bullets">Exit </text><text styleclass="VariableName">MechDesigner </text></li>
            <li styleclass="B Bullets"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Use File-Explorer to navigate to:</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="B Bullets"><text styleclass="VariableName">&lt;CommonAppData&gt;\PSMotion\style</text></para>
          <list id="5" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="3" styleclass="B Bullets" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="B Bullets"><text styleclass="Bullets">Copy </text><text styleclass="VariableName">My-style-name.XML</text><text styleclass="VariableName-IT">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Body Text">to a USB stick</text><text styleclass="VariableName">. </text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="B Bullets"><text styleclass="VariableName" style="color:#ff0000;">You also need to make copies</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo"> of </text><text styleclass="VariableName">MechDesigner.INI</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo"> and </text><text styleclass="VariableName">MechDesigner.XML</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo">.</text></para>
          <list id="6" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="4" styleclass="Bullets" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Bullets">Use File-Explorer to navigate to path:<text styleclass="VariableName"> &lt;LocalAppData&gt; e.g.: C:\users\&lt;user-name&gt;\AppData\Local\PSMotion\IniFiles\</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Bullets">Copy <text styleclass="VariableName">MechDesigner.INI</text><text styleclass="VariableName-IT">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Body Text">and</text><text styleclass="VariableName-IT">&#32;</text><text styleclass="VariableName">MechDesigner.XML </text><text styleclass="Body Text">to the USB stick</text><text styleclass="VariableName">. </text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#343400;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName">On the destination workstation:</para>
          <list id="7" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Bullets" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Bullets"><text styleclass="Body Text">Replace the</text><text styleclass="HowTo NO STEP">&#32;</text><text styleclass="VariableName">MechDesigner.INI</text><text styleclass="VariableName-IT">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Body Text">and</text><text styleclass="VariableName-IT">&#32;</text><text styleclass="VariableName">MechDesigner.XML</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> files on the workstation (see path in </text><text styleclass="VariableName">5</text><text styleclass="Body Text">, above) with the files on your USB stick</text><text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Bullets"><text styleclass="Body Text">Copy and save</text><text styleclass="HowTo NO STEP">&#32;</text><text styleclass="VariableName">My-style-name.XML</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> on your USB stick to the path used for styling: </text><text styleclass="VariableName">&lt;CommonAppData&gt;\PSMotion\style</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Bullets"><text styleclass="Body Text">Start</text><text styleclass="HowTo NO STEP">&#32;</text><text styleclass="VariableName">MechDesigner</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Bullets"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Click </text><text styleclass="T_Menu">Edit menu &gt; Application-Settings : Click the</text><text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text><text styleclass="ParameterHeader">Load</text><text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Body Text">button at the bottom of the dialog.</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Bullets"><text styleclass="Body Text">Explore to </text><text styleclass="VariableName">&lt;CommonAppData&gt;\PSMotion\style\</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Bullets"><text styleclass="Body Text">Find and load </text><text styleclass="VariableName">My-style-name.XML</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">The <text styleclass="VariableName">Theme, Style</text> and <text styleclass="VariableName">Application-Settings</text> are saved automatically as defaults. They load the next time you start <text styleclass="VariableName">MechDesigner</text>.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
